com.engineersbox.httpproxy.resolver.annotation

Annotation Type Handler


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface Handler
    Describes the type of handler a given annotated class is.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      HandlerType value
      Designates the kind of handlers the class has.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract HandlerType value
        Designates the kind of handlers the class has. This can any one the elements of HandlerType. Using the HandlerType.RESPONSE_CONTENT type will mean only response methods annotated with MediaType will be matched when resolving a method for an media type handler. Using the HandlerType.REQUEST_CONTENT value indicates that only request methods with Path annotations and/or HTTP method annotation are used.

        The HTTP method annotations being matched are:
        • GET
        • HEAD
        • OPTIONS
        • POST
        • PUT
        • TRACE
        • UPDATE
        Similarly, only classes annotated with HandlerType.EXCEPTION will be used to match a handler method for exceptions. Specifically methods annotated with ExceptionHandler.
        Returns:
        An element of HandlerType enum
